introduction /ˌɪntrəˈdʌkʃən/

(introductions) 

1. N-COUNT The introduction to a book or talk is the part that comes at the beginning and tells you what the rest of the book or talk is about. 引言; 序 

例： Ellen Malos, in her introduction to 'The Politics of Housework,' provides a summary of the debates. 埃伦·马洛斯在她的《家务政治学》一书的引言中对这些争论做了一个概述。 

2. N-COUNT If you refer to a book as an introduction to a particular subject, you mean that it explains the basic facts about that subject. (书) 入门 

例： The book is a friendly, down-to-earth introduction to physics. 这是一本简明、实用的物理学入门书。 

3. N-COUNT You can refer to a new product as an introduction when it becomes available in a place for the first time. 引进品 

例： There are two among their recent introductions that have greatly impressed me. 他们最新引进的产品中有两件给我留下了深刻的印象。 

4.  →  see also introduce

